<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-40AEE979-41A9-450C-B652-9F3E92FA3BE2" version="3" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-40AEE979-41A9-450C-B652-9F3E92FA3BE2" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">Warranty and contract screen in PRISMAservice</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-52A9E351-C195-4B79-9FEF-0BD3E7F13421" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to find warranty and contract information in PRISMAservice?</title><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the product app of a printer.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Select ‘Warranty and contract’ under ‘Collect printer info’ in the left menu.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">All available info is shown here.
</p></li></ol></section><section id="GUID-9136C620-8C5F-4B82-8879-69D49A3A57EF" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Printer with Standard Warranty</title><fig id="GUID-88073BB3-3DC0-46A5-B7F9-CC195C930CE6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F719864D-8345-4EB3-8353-983D04CDD6BE-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F719864D-8345-4EB3-8353-983D04CDD6BE-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-2A85D6DE-463D-4C66-BDAC-ED1CC4DDA1BA" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Printer with Extended Parts Coverage</title><fig id="GUID-D94E4AF4-8AD0-4F63-9C6A-C6FCBA264E82" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D741831C-3284-495C-9E9B-BCE3FF7D0AA5-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D741831C-3284-495C-9E9B-BCE3FF7D0AA5-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-62C3BAE7-01A3-4568-9C03-86C227A0B76C" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Printer with proCARE contract</title><fig id="GUID-737BE029-2883-49DF-A11A-A49DE7CA1514" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-56DA45CD-6999-4873-9A9E-E8830D46200C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-56DA45CD-6999-4873-9A9E-E8830D46200C-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-D32359C2-9B29-4C73-9F01-7F7C31E5DDF5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Claim warranty for an active part</title><p class="- topic/p ">Select one part from the list of active parts and press ‘Claim warranty’ button:
</p><fig id="GUID-F86B8673-1207-4778-BFD8-4BF8B46325FC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-8CDDB4EB-483B-4676-A0A7-A74F95390B30-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8CDDB4EB-483B-4676-A0A7-A74F95390B30-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The warranty result is presented in a pop-up screen.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The result can be:
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Approve
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">When in standard warranty, LQF form is presented for download to facilitate warranty process.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">When in standard warranty, part must be returned to Venlo.
</p></li></ul></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Reject
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">No warranty, part may be covered by proCARE, otherwise it must be invoiced
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> A warranty reject reason is shown (e.g. print volume &gt; 20.000 sqm)
</p></li></ul></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Undetermined
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The data is too old to reliably determine warranty
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure printer is correctly connected to PRISMAservice
</p></li></ul></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">When warranty is approved and the part must returned to Venlo, a link to the LQF form is presented:
</p><fig id="GUID-91C44F3D-BC0A-4954-854D-581FEBB93044" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6E81A42B-403C-40CF-B67B-FD9473D89BBD-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6E81A42B-403C-40CF-B67B-FD9473D89BBD-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-8ABBEE09-6B1C-447F-9862-C81C212D7E3F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5022089F-5A2E-4B7D-98F7-467D97AE7277-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5022089F-5A2E-4B7D-98F7-467D97AE7277-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-C2E4AD33-36AC-4A76-BCFA-77AAEBB95F70" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Claim warranty for a replaced part</title><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Not supported by the UI
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-916ABCD4-E20B-4B44-BE6E-2FEEDC7DA89C" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Claim warranty for an active Printhead</title><p class="- topic/p "> Select a printhead in the list of active printheads and press 'replace printhead' button:
</p><fig id="GUID-3C472399-1F21-4EB7-9CD1-6DE5AF8B18AF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6D98D4CE-B675-46D6-AF66-D990B7B20795-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6D98D4CE-B675-46D6-AF66-D990B7B20795-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">An overview is presented with the printhead serial number and the position to confirm that you check the desired printhead:
</p><fig id="GUID-8A5C0C9E-D13F-447A-9E07-B16F83F8A48D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-67E6AC9A-A79C-4B79-A788-AEF7DAF72A45-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-67E6AC9A-A79C-4B79-A788-AEF7DAF72A45-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Press on ‘check warranty’:
</p><fig id="GUID-6BECB79C-97BA-48DE-803B-29B3B7754829" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2A16532C-9AF1-42D7-9118-5B14AE4261BB-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2A16532C-9AF1-42D7-9118-5B14AE4261BB-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The result is presented in the pop-up.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In case of approved warranty, a link to the LQF form is also shown:
</p><fig id="GUID-37839A36-36DE-409D-9489-6BB660EF680E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-31241BAB-39B0-4E0F-B381-B8FD7916E4C2-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-31241BAB-39B0-4E0F-B381-B8FD7916E4C2-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-3190BB06-2975-4E20-A527-336A972EEEFF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5022089F-5A2E-4B7D-98F7-467D97AE7277-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5022089F-5A2E-4B7D-98F7-467D97AE7277-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">If no, not enough or no recent data is available to determine warranty, the UI shows a warning (without a warranty result):
</p><fig id="GUID-D9FE2864-AD72-4A38-A63D-8534B32265E1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E9D3FC5B-FB33-4C2B-AEC6-18E2BE59FC44-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E9D3FC5B-FB33-4C2B-AEC6-18E2BE59FC44-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-F5D021E8-73BC-419F-B652-901F1D67488C" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Claim warranty for a replaced Printhead</title><p class="- topic/p ">The result column indicates how the PH costs are handled:
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Warranty: PH is covered by (any form of) warranty.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> ProCare: PH is covered by the PH budget of the proCARE contract.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Invoice: PH is neither covered by Warranty nor by proCARE and must be invoiced.
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">For PHs with result ‘Warranty’ it is still possible to claim warranty via PRISMAservice using the ‘claim warranty button on the replaced PH:
</p><fig id="GUID-F43AE66E-4CEE-43FF-B924-AF1C6653C587" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F8FCBBDC-85F5-4ABC-9B6B-93C62CE07E56-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F8FCBBDC-85F5-4ABC-9B6B-93C62CE07E56-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The ‘claim warranty’ button is inactive when a replaced PH is selected that has a result ‘ProCare’ or ‘Invoice’.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">You cannot claim on a PH that is already replaced and warranty is rejected.
</p><fig id="GUID-C2A1EDB5-B2AB-47BD-A740-12D249A5D9C6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5CBF5758-2250-4D7C-84F9-61B12353A1E0-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5CBF5758-2250-4D7C-84F9-61B12353A1E0-low.png"/></fig></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-9562CDA3-B0A7-45BA-8B3B-F563A3681F22.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>proCARE</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</concept>